usUserHome = System.getProperty(\"user.home\");\n        System.setProperty(\"user.home\", temporaryHome.toString());\n        if (lines.length > 0) {\n            Files.writeString(temporaryHome.resolve(\"junit.properties\"), String.join(System.lineSeparator(), lines));\n        }\n        return new ExposedTestRunner();\n    }\n\n    public static class RecordingFailureDetailView implements FailureDetailView {\n        private final JLabel component = new JLabel(\"failure details\");\n\n        @Override\n        public void clear() {\n            component.setText(\"\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Component getComponent() {\n            return component;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void showFailure(TestFailure failure) {\n            component.setText(failure.toString());\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class EmptyTestCollector implements TestCollector {\n        static int createdInstances;\n\n        public EmptyTestCollector() {\n            createdInstances++;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Enumeration collectTests() {\n            return Collections.enumeration(Collections.emptyList());\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ReloadableTestCase extends TestCase {\n        static final List<String> constructedNames = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        public ReloadableTestCase(String name) {\n            super(name);\n            constructedNames.add(name);\n        }\n\n        public void testNeverRuns() {\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static class ExposedTestRunner extends TestRunner {\n        FailureDetailView newFailureDetailView() {\n            return createFailureDetailView();\n        }\n\n        JLabel newLogo() {\n            return createLogo();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777934661066}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring dialog interactions**\n\nI'm thinking about how to dispose of any dialog with the title \"About.\" If I don't find it right away, I might need to repeat until it appears. I wonder if using a latch could help here? Also, I need to remember that timer events fire on EDT. If `doClick` is on the test thread, can the EDT handle it? I think calling `item.doClick(0)` on the test thread triggers the action synchronously rather than on the EDT.\n\n**Considering exception handling**\n\nI could consider using `CountDownLatch` with `finished.countDown()` in the `finally` block. I'll wait for 5 seconds, but there's a potential issue: if no display is available or a `HeadlessException` is thrown in the Event Dispatch Thread (EDT), the latch counts down without showing a dialog, which may cause the test to fail based on existing assumptions about the display. I also need to capture exceptions with `AtomicReference<Throwable>`, but exceptions in `invokeLater` won’t propagate, so I should catch `Throwable`.\n\n**Inspecting test utilities**\n\nI'm considering whether I need fully qualified imports. The AGENTS seems to suggest importing classes, so that’s something to explore. I think it might help to inspect the existing TestRunnerTest for possible insights into utility styles. It's a bit of a puzzle, but I'm looking forward to putting the pieces together and figuring out the best approach!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d78c524247685cf0169f921304724819f96926be05e742a27\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-SFEgGl-ka-CZLixVzWCRmLPefFAN6828yEjD29qFYAINRnM3Defh_ofVVfYM2e_5aQmYHizJ3JhUUWVPryyIgCjkmK_2vIroO-LHhgnPeuPBn9yh770CQApc2agZfWnnm6BphaT6pr8phUW4d1mFGe5NhYfZOoywNw5PSe9LZwQT6dyaZQrElf5QIfXEEXCQ4koFcGC9ipIhXY4rm-mZlTvsIPuDiqRWcqghGJWplbUwvJ0MU2qHhIt392WGBBzG3WOvbRAYfT0xnb-yDQ62slrmu5Y2qPfTn55E6uEy4vCG-NqyGbPTzIXC_jpz33EH2-EMYfcz3gWnsbgbq9o